entually the whole haystack was flat, the the policeman, the local policeman caught us one night and the magistrate went round or tent the policeman round to all the parents houses and said, well I'm not taking 'em to court as long as the fathers'll pay s
e
ven and sixpence towards the damage they've done. Well you can baer in mind that 1911 seven and sixpence was a lot of money. So my father paid the seven and six out. But he took seven and six worth out of my bottom. I knew that I'd had it. I didn't do it 
